14:01.974 --> 14:04.068
Bravissimo! They're great!

14:04.177 --> 14:06.270
They get the job
starting tonight.

14:06.379 --> 14:08.347
(cheering)

14:08.448 --> 14:10.279
LEATHER: All right, girls.
That's enough. Now get going.

14:10.383 --> 14:11.248
- Go get your costumes.
- Okay.

14:11.351 --> 14:12.340
Wait a minute, girls,

14:12.452 --> 14:13.749
we'll give you a ride
in the car.

14:13.853 --> 14:15.082
- All right.
- Yeah, great.

14:15.188 --> 14:17.349
Can I sit next to the kid
with the top hat?

14:17.457 --> 14:19.448
Sure.

14:21.360 --> 14:24.262
She's yours, Potsie.

14:28.534 --> 14:30.764
Huh? Well, now,
what did I tell you?

14:30.870 --> 14:32.770
Fonz, I-isn't she good?
What do you say?

14:32.872 --> 14:36.069
Don't you get yourself excited.

14:36.175 --> 14:38.405
Just 'cause she's doing music
don't mean she went straight.

14:38.511 --> 14:41.674
I heard Al Capone was an
accomplished harmonica player.

14:43.516 --> 14:45.416
Hey, Al, Al, did you hire
the girls yet?

14:45.518 --> 14:46.713
Yeah, they're great.

14:46.819 --> 14:48.913
Oh, boy, are you in trouble.

14:49.021 --> 14:50.785
Trouble? Now wait a minute,
I got nothing in writing.

14:50.890 --> 14:51.982
No, no, don't panic, Al.

14:52.091 --> 14:53.320
Wh-What's the trouble?

14:53.426 --> 14:56.157
Well, I heard through
the grapevine that Officer Kirk

14:56.262 --> 15:00.165
is gonna close down Al's place
if he hires any, uh, ex-cons.

15:00.266 --> 15:01.995
All right, that's it.

15:02.101 --> 15:03.000
Forget it.

15:03.102 --> 15:04.035
I knew it.

15:04.137 --> 15:05.229
Let's just forget
the whole thing.

15:05.338 --> 15:06.328
Yeah, that-that's a good idea.

15:06.439 --> 15:07.338
We should just forget it.

15:07.440 --> 15:09.067
Hold it.
Time out here. Hold it.

15:09.175 --> 15:11.337
I don't want to hear any talking
about throwing in the towel.

15:11.444 --> 15:13.913
Fonz, Officer Kirk!

15:14.013 --> 15:16.243
I'll take care of Officer Kirk,
all right?

15:16.349 --> 15:18.112
Leather and the Suedes
are playing here Friday night

15:18.217 --> 15:20.208
and that's final.

15:27.059 --> 15:29.551
(siren wailing)

15:34.133 --> 15:36.466
All right,
out of my way, Delvecchio.

15:36.569 --> 15:37.866
I gotta talk to these people.

15:37.970 --> 15:39.597
Oh, come on, Officer Kirk.

15:39.705 --> 15:42.174
Can't we discuss this
over an Arnoldburger?

15:42.275 --> 15:45.335
Making death threats, eh?

15:46.813 --> 15:49.646
I'll get you for that,
Delvecchio.

15:49.749 --> 15:51.342
All right, now, hear this.

15:51.450 --> 15:54.284
There's a decadent rock-and-roll
group working here tonight.

15:54.387 --> 15:57.686
We don't like
undesirable people, do we?

15:57.790 --> 15:59.190
They're very undesirable.

15:59.292 --> 16:01.226
We don't like undesirables.

16:01.327 --> 16:03.159
I'm a very unhappy man
right now.

16:03.262 --> 16:05.822
And when I'm unhappy,
I like to write tickets.

16:05.932 --> 16:07.900
Lots and lots of tickets.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.195
How does that hit you?

16:09.302 --> 16:11.202
Now, sound off after me.

16:11.304 --> 16:13.795
Go home, jailbirds.

16:13.906 --> 16:16.307
- CROWD: Go home, jailbirds.
- Come on. Let's hit it!

16:16.409 --> 16:18.241
CROWD:
Go home, jailbirds.

16:18.344 --> 16:20.176
-(chanting): Go home, jailbirds!
- What's going on here?

16:20.279 --> 16:22.111
It's Kirk.
He's making the kids do this.

16:22.215 --> 16:24.115
Fonz, it's Leather.
She won't go on.

16:24.217 --> 16:26.117
- KIRK: I can't hear you
out there! -Go home, jailbirds!

16:26.219 --> 16:29.552
Go home, jailbirds!
Go home, jailbirds!

16:29.655 --> 16:32.557
- Go home, jailbirds! Go home,
jailbirds! -KIRK: Let's hear it!

16:32.658 --> 16:33.887
Why aren't you out there
singing?

16:33.993 --> 16:35.825
Why aren't you making
with the golden tones?

16:35.928 --> 16:38.022
Can't you hear those creeps
out there yelling at us,

16:38.130 --> 16:39.359
"Go home, jailbirds"?

16:39.465 --> 16:41.160
I thought you said
you could handle the cop!

16:41.267 --> 16:42.826
I can, but I won't.

16:42.935 --> 16:44.426
That'll solve your problem
tonight.

16:44.537 --> 16:46.096
What about tomorrow night?
What about next week?

16:46.205 --> 16:49.107
It's time for you to stand up
for your rights, right now.

16:49.208 --> 16:52.439
I have had enough hassles
in my life-- forget it.

16:52.545 --> 16:55.105
Oh, well, I'm sorry.
My mistake.

16:55.214 --> 16:57.877
And I thought that there was
some hope for you.

16:57.984 --> 17:00.009
- You did?
- I wouldn't be standing here

17:00.119 --> 17:02.611
in the middle of the ladies'
room talking to you if I didn't.

17:02.722 --> 17:04.713
Are you gonna forget
about the wallet?

17:04.824 --> 17:06.656
Hey, like I always say,

17:06.759 --> 17:10.888
to err is human,
to forgive is divine.

17:10.997 --> 17:13.157
Now, why don't you just go
right out there

17:13.266 --> 17:15.393
and sing me a song?

17:15.501 --> 17:17.401
- KIRK: Come on! Let's hit it!
- Go home, jailbirds!

17:17.502 --> 17:19.198
- Go home, jailbirds!
- Can't you hear

17:19.305 --> 17:20.795
what that cop
is doing out there?

17:20.906 --> 17:23.808
I'm not ready for that yet.

17:23.910 --> 17:26.810
Whoa.

17:26.913 --> 17:29.245
Then you're a loser.

17:29.348 --> 17:32.079
Listen, Mr. Magic, I'm not you.

17:32.184 --> 17:35.313
I can't control things
with a finger snap.

17:35.421 --> 17:37.389
Hey, that didn't come to me
right away.

17:37.490 --> 17:39.049
It took time, at least...

17:39.158 --> 17:41.286
two nights.

17:42.328 --> 17:43.818
Well, things are different
for me.

17:43.930 --> 17:47.491
Good luck has always been
kind of scarce.

17:47.600 --> 17:49.625
Oh, yeah.

17:49.735 --> 17:51.965
Well, look, don't give me
that bit about, uh,

17:52.071 --> 17:53.903
